map.string: This entity has a gravel area defined.
This is a spawn point. New entities are created here.
The terrain can be altered by editing terrain points. Here's a mound.
Lakes can be created by lowering height points below the water line.
Demonstration of the "attached" attributes. The clothing of the entity is determined by the inventory entities that are attached.
This is a spawner. It will check every five seconds if there are at least two granite rocks within a 10 meters radius. If not, it will spawn one. Try to delete one of the rocks.
This bear has an "immortal" property and cannot be killed. Try to delete it.
This is a spawn area used for respawning. Check the human to the right.
This human has a respawning property set to the area to the left. When killed he'll respawn there. Try to delete him.
This terrainmod is using fixed positioning, level type and height 3.
This terrainmod is using relative positioning, fixed type and height 3.
This terrainmod is using fixed positioning, adjust type and height 3.
This terrainmod is using relative positioning, level type and height 3.
These are the default terrain area types available.
Entities of the same type can have different appearances depending on their properties.
Demonstrates how attributes can be set on spawned entities. The dog has a transient property of 5, which means it will be deleted after five seconds.
Shows the goal 'patrol' which makes the entity patrol two points.
Aims to demonstrate how a character navigates obstacles to patrol between three points. If the human is stuck it means that we need to improve the path finding.
This is a demo world, meant to showcase different features of the Worldforge system.
Shows entity filter goals. The human is told to gather mushrooms, but only those belonging to the species amanita. New amanitas are created by the spawner.
